Variation.
Males may vary in the outer margins of tegmina and body shape (including tegmina). Most specimens we examined with dense brownish muddy maculae on the outer margins of tegmina (
Fig. 6 A
), but some specimens with less muddy parts (
Fig. 6 H
). The body shape varied, most individuals (from Shigatse) with broad body and short tegmina, but we also examined specimens with slender body and longer tegmina. Females differs in the coloration, the specimens with coloration ranging from orange to dark brown.
